# MODULE 2: Exponents, Order of Operations, and Algebraic Expressions

## 2.1 Exponents

### What You Need to Know

An exponent tells you how many times to multiply a number by itself.

**2⁵** means: 2 × 2 × 2 × 2 × 2 = 32

| Term | Base | Exponent | Meaning |
|------|------|----------|---------|
| 3⁴ | 3 | 4 | 3 × 3 × 3 × 3 = 81 |
| (-2)³ | -2 | 3 | (-2) × (-2) × (-2) = -8 |
| -2⁴ | 2 | 4 | -(2 × 2 × 2 × 2) = -16 |

