## 4.2 Solutions to Linear Equations in Two Variables

### What Makes an Ordered Pair a Solution?

An ordered pair is a solution if substituting the values makes the equation true.

### Example: Checking Solutions

Is (-1, 3) a solution to 4x + 5y = 11?

4(-1) + 5(3) = -4 + 15 = 11 ✓ Yes!

Is (3/2, 5) a solution?
4(3/2) + 5(5) = 6 + 25 = 31 ≠ 11 ✗ No!

