## 9.2 Multiplying and Dividing Rational Expressions

### Multiplication

1. Factor all numerators and denominators
2. Multiply numerators, multiply denominators
3. Simplify

**Example:** (x² - 4)/(x² - x - 2) × (x + 1)/(x - 2)
= (x + 2)(x - 2)/(x - 2)(x + 1) × (x + 1)/(x - 2)
= (x + 2)/(x - 2)

### Division

1. Keep first fraction
2. Change to multiplication
3. Flip (reciprocal) second fraction
4. Multiply and simplify

**Example:** (x² - 9)/(x² - 4) ÷ (x - 3)/(x + 2)
= (x² - 9)/(x² - 4) × (x + 2)/(x - 3)
= (x + 3)(x - 3)/[(x - 2)(x + 2)] × (x + 2)/(x - 3)
= (x + 3)/(x - 2)

